RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOSTLY HARMLESS broke out and brushed with a foe then was corrected, was taken in hand when the pacesetter crossed in front early then moved out, tracked the pace on the outside, made a bid in the three path around the turn, took the lead outside the quarter-pole, spun five wide into the stretch then drifted further out while shaking clear, extended the advantage under a strong hand-ride into the final furlong, was given one pop of the crop outside the sixteenth-pole then was placed back under a brisk hand-ride while much the best. AFILADA was last to commence then dropped back, settled on the outside, moved up late on the backstretch, was asked in the four path around the turn, chased six wide into the stretch then moved further out in pursuit of the winner and proved no match while able to hold the place. GRACEFULLY WILD bumped with a rival at the start, dropped back early then was taken back before angling in outside the five-eighths, went three wide around the turn, shifted six wide coming to the quarter-pole, dropped in behind horses in upper stretch and missed the place while well clear for the show. CAIAROSSA showed speed then was taken in hand, raced just off the pace, drafted inside around the turn, was asked for her best in upper stretch and came up empty. BECAUSEOFTHEBRAVE broke in and bumped with a foe, moved in while going to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, vied in the two path around the turn, lost the advantage to the winner outside the quarter-pole and faded. SARAH'S PRIDE was coaxed along off the pace, traveled around the turn in the two path, came out some into upper stretch and failed to respond.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 45000. (UP TO $7,830 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACH ONE chased along the inside early on until tipped to the three path half a mile from home, raced outside the leader through the turn four wide and was floated briefly five wide three furlongs from home, advanced to take command near the quarter pole and went six wide into upper stretch, then drew clear under a drive to prevail. HATCH broke in a step at the start tightening up the lane of BERT BERT BERT in tandem with MACH ONE, prompted the leader from the inside in the two path, came under coaxing near the five-sixteenths, spun two to three wide for home and weakened in the late stages while along for the place honors. MAURITIUS showed the way in hand five then four wide under prompting to the inside, tucked three wide into the turn, floated four wide midway carrying MACH ONE briefly five wide, got displaced from command and went four wide into upper stretch, then weakened in the drive. BERT BERT BERT got his lane tightened up at the start when HATCH broke in a step, grew detached at the tail of the field saving ground when devoid of speed, remained along the inside through the turn and into upper stretch, made some headway on the top trio while trailing throughout.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CURLINS CHOIR went to the front, set the pace under pressure to her outside, vied along the rail on the turn, dueled inside of the runner-up in the stretch, disposed of that foe into the final sixteenth and proved best under strong urging. SICILIAN GRANDMA chased the pace on the outside, gained in the four path around the turn, made a bid while dropping to the three path outside the quarter-pole, came inward in upper stretch, battled outside of the runner-up to the sixteenth-pole and was outfinished while clear for the place. OUR ROSIE DIAMONDS bumped twice with a rival at the start, was urged along off the pace, went around most of the turn in the two path, shifted three then four wide late on that bend, came five wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response while best of the rest. AUDIT COMMITTEE bumped twice with an opponent at the start, was urged along on the outside, went five wide on the turn, spun six wide into the stretch, chased into the final furlong and capitulated then was not urged from outside the sixteenth-pole to the wire. JESSICA'S RACE was urged along at the rear, raced inside to the three path around the turn, came four wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. LADY QUINN broke through the front of the gate prior to the start and sat down on her hindquarters at the same time, was deemed fit to run by the state veterinarian, pressed the pace on the outside then in the three path on the turn, dropped back near the five-sixteenths, moved to the two path outside the quarter-pole and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJESTIC TIGER coaxed from the gate, chased five then four wide advancing on the front midway on the turn to take command when placed to coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled in spinning just off the inside into upper stretch, drew clear under a drive to prevail and was geared down in the late stages. JADE'S DREAM chased four then three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, continued four then three wide for home, proved no match for the top one, dug in knocking heads to the finish with PRINCE OF JOY and ultimately bested that foe in the final jumps to procure the place honors. PRINCE OF JOY chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun just off the inside for home, proved no match for the top one, dug in head to head to the finish but was bested at the end and forced to settle for the show honors. EL MAYOR showed the way in hand three then two wide coming under pressure when put to coaxing near the five-sixteenths, yielded command at that station, spun three then two wide into upper stretch and weakened. EXXTOP chased two to three wide, came under coaxing three to four wide at the three-eighths, went five wide into upper stretch and trailed.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR. KRAFT chased the pace down the backstretch, went two then three wide around the turn, dropped to the rail at the quarter-pole, pursued the leader against the fence in upper stretch, was guided out over the heels of that foe into the final furlong, gained into the final sixteenth and got up under strong urging. LAUNCH CONTROL broke in and bumped with a foe then was hustled to the lead, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked in the three then two path around the turn, led under a drive into the final sixteenth but was denied while clear for the place. ELECTRIC STUFF settled off the pace while showing some dislike of the kickback, was urged three to four wide around the turn, pursued the top two in the stretch and finished willingly for the show. CHALKY CAT was bumped at the start and forced in then taken up while in tight, spotted the front several lengths, moved up on the outside under urging, chased in the five path around the turn and weakened. GEM MINT TEN was fractious behind the gate, showed good speed then disputed the pace, dropped back near the half-mile pole, chased inside around the turn, came out into upper stretch then was carried inward and tired. AWESOME FORCE climbed some outside the five-eighths, was urged along off the pace, went four wide on the turn and came up empty. FERRIS MULER broke in and hit the gate, settled under some urging, moved out leaving the backstretch, moved from the two path to the four path around the turn and was no factor. BINGOOD TO KNOWYA chased the pace, dropped back late on the backstretch, came up empty in the two path on the turn and retreated.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRISONER coaxed from the gate, showed the way from the two path until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, edged away under a drive to the eighth pole, dug in drifting out in the final sixteenth while holding well to the finish. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIMELESS JOURNEY went around the first turn in the two path, settled off the pace, drafted inside on the far turn, was given her cue at the five-sixteenths, came through a rail opening to make a bid approaching the quarter-pole, took over into upper stretch, drifted out outside the furlong marker, responded well into the final sixteenth and held under strong urging. MOMMASGOTTARUN rounded the first turn in the two path, prompted the pace down the backstretch, steadied then dropped back in crowded quarters leaving the backstretch, came under intermittent urging in the two path around the far turn, was roused for more at the five-sixteenths, shifted four wide into the stretch then quickly moved to the six path, swapped back to her inside lead inside the furlong marker and finished willingly for the place. LET HER INSPIRE U was hustled from the gate, went three wide on the first turn, tracked the pace on the outside, made a bid in the three path on the far turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, pursued the winner into the final furlong and weakened but was clear for the show. FAR AWAY LOVE (ARG) went to the front, raced inside on the first turn, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked in the two path on the far turn, lost the advantage to the winner into upper stretch and gave way. ICE PRINCESS dropped back shortly after the start, went two then three wide around the first turn, settled at the rear, was urged three wide early on the far turn then shifted five wide, remained five wide into the stretch and failed to rally. SOFIA'S SECRET was rated four then three wide on the first turn, settled outside down the backstretch, chased four wide around the far turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OVERSTEP three wide in aim of the front early on, advanced to take over command half a mile from home and tucked to the two path through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun three wide into upper stretch, drew clear under a drive to prevail. SIMPLY chased three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, went eight wide into upper stretch, proved no match for the top one while running on to secure the place honors. MASON MANIA chased two to three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch, kept on to procure the show honors. TIMBUKTU chased three to four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, went six wide into upper stretch and stayed on one paced to the finish. SON OF AN EX chased just off the inside detached at the rear of the field for the opening half mile, came under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch and improved position to the finish. DR. MARBOOZ six paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked four wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, went nine wide into upper stretch and weakened. ROYAL SUSPECT chased along the inside under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, made no impact. UNO forwardly placed four then three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went seven wide into upper stretch, tired. THE REVENGER chased four paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn coming under coaxing three furlongs out, went seven wide into upper stretch and tired. HERE'S WALDO broke out at the start, showed brief speed crossing to show the way in hand along the inside, got displaced from the front and tipped to the two path through the turn getting placed to coaxing midway, swung four wide into upper stretch and folded.
